"Motor oil body, black and viscous; deep mahogany head of thick (though fleeting) cream. A twirl of the glass leaves lots of legs but little lacing, promising a big, boozy drink. Hell of nose if you have a sweet tooth: massive maple syrup, chocolate frosting, cherry cordial, and vanilla-heavy, oaky bourbon scents. Not a doughnut shop, but a candy factory…one with a Willy Wonka that loved booze. The palate follows suit, a wave of gooey fudge, mocha, and sugar cookie. Bring it all together and you get, yep, a little bit of doughnut; that, plus campfire smoke, toasted oak, and a hint of mint. Finishes with a lingering sugary tone, a rich gourmet dark chocolate sticking thick to the tongue. A sugar rush of a drink, and one hell of a dessert. Cheers!"
""
