""
"this is great beer, on par i think with the biscotti beers, but this adds an extra twist. not sure how its done, are real doughnuts really added to the kettle, i dont really get it, but when i think about it, i taste glazed breakfast treats in here, and i agree with others about its almost waxy texture. hershey syrup in color, smallish mocha head, strange nose. i almost smell chili pepper actually, among some cocoa notes and the evil twin base porter that is just enormous. bitterness abounds, and i find myself happy that this isnt dessert sweet, its only a little sugary, and it cleans up well. i taste an almost spice too, not sure if its the alcohol manifesting itself in a weird way or what, but its there, especially in the finish among the forest of roasted bitterness. yet another beer that blurs the already fuzzy line between porter and stout. also, not extremely different from the biscotti breaks, just sweeter with a more pronounced cocoa or dark chocolate profile. maybe not as doughnut forward as i wanted, but how can a beer really be doughnut forward anyway? i guess this is as close as it gets, for now... huge body, sticky feel, milkshake density, long finish. enjoyable, but a bottle that you must not drink alone."
