"O: another interesting take on the Imperial Biscotti Break brand, sure to appeal more to some than others, and certainly worth the try if you've got the dough ;)"
"Poured into a Reuben's Brew snifter. Pours a very dark mahogany brown, appearing black in the glass, with a thin light brown head with good retention with light lacing. Nice aroma of chocolate and dark toasty malt, very much like a high quality dark chocolate donut. Flavor also emphasizes chocolate, with a definate cake like element; baker's yeast. Chocolate glaze, eggy brownies, vanilla, hints of coffee. Complex, but in the chocolate / cocoa universe. Good medium creamy body. A flavorful, chocolate forward imperial stout that is very nicely integrated. It may just be the power of suggestion, but I did detect cake donut flavors in this stout. Creamy and rich, this is a great addition to an already well loved series of stouts. ABV completely and dangerously covered. Donut."
""
"Yes, this beer drinker humbly presents the case that glazed doughnuts are very prominent on the palate of this beer. And yes, it is indeed a tasty drinking experience. It would have been even better had the alcohol not been as present on the finish, and the nose could have been much more aromatic. Not anywhere near the gluttonous level of Mornin' Delight or Dark Lord for example. And the body is a little light for the offering, need even more creaminess, heft, and stickiness for something that is supposed to be so gluttonous. Still, I am thoroughly impressed by the execution of this glazed doughnut imperial stout. Seek. This. Out!"
"This one pours a full bodied midnight black with a two finger dark mocha head. It looks like you'd want a beer of this size. This nose is big and rich. There is smooth roast, light coffee, and sweet chocolate glazed doughnut. I was skeptical about doughnut character being present in the nose but there actually is chocolate doughnut. The flavors are very well integrated. It drinks like a liquid chocolate glazed doughnut with a touch of roast. There isn't any alcohol presence whatsoever. It's delicious. The body is perfect. It's big and so smooth. Overall I think this is fantastic. I enjoyed this just as much as the Biscotti, if not more."
